blueprint/src/chapters/AbelJacobi.tex:44:  The Lean closure is the field projection from the Albanese structure $\mathrm{IsAlbanese}\,C\,P\,\Jac(C)$ supplied by Theorem~\ref{thm:nonempty_jacobianWitness}. By Definition~\ref{def:IsAlbanese}, this predicate carries among its data the assertion $P \circ \iota_P = \eta_{\Jac(C)}$ that the universal pointed morphism sends the marked point to the identity of the target group scheme. Since $\alpha_P := \iota_P$ by Definition~\ref{def:ofCurve}, the claim is precisely the pointed-property field of that Albanese structure.
